lerMount-150x92.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MicroControllerMount-768x469.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 483px) 100vw, 483px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, attach the microcontroller board using three machine screws as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MicroController.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MicroController.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2047\" width=\"461\" height=\"337\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MicroController.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MicroController-300x219.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MicroController-150x110.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MicroController-768x562.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 461px) 100vw, 461px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then insert the STM32 microcontroller into the socket as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Microcontroller2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Microcontroller2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2048\" width=\"460\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Microcontroller2.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Microcontroller2-300x197.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Microcontroller2-150x98.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Microcontroller2-768x504.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 460px) 100vw, 460px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, prepare the wires for the limit switches. Cut two 14 inch long pieces of 2 wire 28 gauge ribbon wire and attach the connectors to the end as shown. Note that we use 3 pin connectors here but attach only two wires to each.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LimitSwitchWires.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LimitSwitchWires.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2051\" width=\"466\" height=\"327\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LimitSwitchWires.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LimitSwitchWires-300x210.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LimitSwitchWires-150x105.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LimitSwitchWires-768x539.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 466px) 100vw, 466px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then solder the other end of the wires to the limit switches as shown below, the order of the wires is not important here. Note the zip ties which attach the wires to the turret. These zip ties provide strain relief for the solder joints.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LimitSwitchesSolder.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LimitSwitchesSolder-1024x394.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2054\" width=\"467\" height=\"180\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LimitSwitchesSolder-1024x394.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LimitSwitchesSolder-300x115.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LimitSwitchesSolder-150x58.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LimitSwitchesSolder-768x295.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LimitSwitchesSolder.jpg 1300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 467px) 100vw, 467px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now we are going to attach and wire the three <strong>Motor Controllers<\/strong>. Attach a <strong>Motor Controller<\/strong> for the<strong> Drive Motors <\/strong>to the underside of the chassis. Then attach the power and control wires as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MotorController1Comgo.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MotorController1Comgo-1024x377.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2078\" width=\"591\" height=\"217\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MotorController1Comgo-1024x377.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MotorController1Comgo-300x111.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MotorController1Comgo-150x55.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MotorController1Comgo-768x283.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MotorController1Comgo-1536x566.jpg 1536w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MotorController1Comgo.jpg 1628w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 591px) 100vw, 591px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next we attach a <strong>Motor Controller<\/strong> that will control the <strong>Feeder <\/strong>and <strong>Shooter <\/strong>motors and attach the power and control wires as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MotorController2combo.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MotorController2combo-1024x381.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2076\" width=\"604\" height=\"224\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MotorController2combo-1024x381.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MotorController2combo-300x112.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MotorController2combo-150x56.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/MotorController2combo-768x286.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-